

	 
        I pick a daisy,     gently, carefully, it might just break if i'm not careful. i cup it in my hand, the yellow in the middle reflects the sun, the white petal so clean and fresh. the sky above me broods with grey and white clouds in turmoil, strangely, the sun is never covered... it starts to rain, still the sun covers me, so long as i hold onto my daisy.            don't crush the daisies while you're walking through the garden...     
    
